      >
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Reverse Air</h2>
          <p class="text-grisT font-thin text-sm lg:text-lg md:text-lg">
            A cleaning system that directs low-pressure air in the opposite
            direction to remove dust from the filter bags, typically used in
            larger baghouses or high-dust applications.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Pulse Jet</h2>
          <p class="text-grisT font-thin text-sm lg:text-lg md:text-lg">
            A cleaning system that uses short bursts of compressed air to
            dislodge dust and debris from the filter bags, maintaining
            continuous airflow and filtration efficiency.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="w-full bg-grisT text-white flex flex-col gap-6">
    <div
      class="max-w-7xl px-8 mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 items-center py-6"
    >
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl">Triaso Supersonic Nozzle</h2><br />
        <p class="text-sm lg:text-lg md:text-lg font-thin">
          Our supersonic nozzles are 3D printed in-house using carbon alloy
          materials for exceptional resistance to impacts, high temperatures,
          and vibrations. Ensuring highly efficient fine particle collection in
          the baghouse.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="w-full flex justify-center items-center">
        <Image
          src={boquillasVL}
          alt="Triaso Supersonic Nozzle"
          class="full rounded-xl"
        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-full">
      <div
        class="max-w-7xl px-8 mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 items-start rounded-lg mb-5 w-full lg:w-[50%] md:w-[50%] gap-10"
      >
        <AcordeonItemCol
          title="Typical Venturi System"
          bgColor="bg-bgBeige"
          image={img5.src}
          imageClassName="pb-[50px]"
          client:only
        >
          <div class="w-full py-10 text-sm md:text-base text-grisT">
            <p>
              In venturi-based filtration systems, the airflow design introduces
              multiple inefficiencies that affect both dust collection and
              system durability. The high-speed airflow exiting the venturi
              creates a low-pressure zone at the upper section of the filter
              bag, pulling dust toward that area. This causes uneven
              accumulation and reduces filtration capacity. Over time, fine
              particles become embedded deep within the fabric, making cleaning
              less effective.
            </p><br />
            <p>
              Another issue is the placement of the cleaning air pulse near the
              bag opening. This location limits its ability to draw in
              additional air that could improve dust removal. Meanwhile, the
              narrow venturi forces filtered air to accelerate rapidly into the
              plenum, creating upward airflow that resists the cleaning pulse.
              As a result, stronger air blasts are needed, increasing energy use
              and putting mechanical stress on the bags—leading to faster wear
              and reduced lifespan.
            </p>
          </div>
        </AcordeonItemCol>
        <AcordeonItemCol
          title="Triaso High Ratio System"
          bgColor="bg-bgBeige"
          image={img6.src}
          client:only
        >
          <div class="w-full py-10 text-sm md:text-base text-grisT">
            <p>
              The new series baghouse improves dust removal by completely
              redesigning the airflow process. Instead of relying on a
              traditional venturi system, it uses a supersonic
              converging-diverging nozzle to generate the cleaning air jet. This
              shift in design allows for the induction of more secondary air,
              enhancing the cleaning efficiency. The removal of the venturi also
              reduces the throat velocity at the bag’s inlet, preventing the
              negative pressure that typically leads to dust buildup at the top
              of the filter bag.
            </p><br />
            <p>
              By fully utlization of the bag mouth, the cleaning air jet expands
              evenly, minimizing the likelihood of dust cake blowout. Leading to
              a more uniform bag inflation, resulting in a more effective
              cleaning cycle and reduced wear on the fabric. As a result, the
              Triaso Model only requires half the filter area compared to
              traditional venturi systems, enabling Triaso to offer high
              performance in a more compact form.
            </p>
          </div>
        </AcordeonItemCol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <br />
  <div class="w-full px-8 text-center">
    <h2
