                designed for controlled horizontal and downward airflow. This
                configuration prevents re-entrainment of fine material. A
                knockout chamber slows the airflow, allowing heavier particles
                to settle in the hopper, while internal baffles distribute air
                evenly and protect the filter bags from abrasion.
